quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  11,98,"He shall approach his people on the resurrection day, and take them down to water at the Fire,- an evil watering-place to water at"
  11,99,In this (world) were they followed by a curse; and on the resurrection day evil shall be the aid they are aided with
  11,100,That is one of the stories of the cities which we recite to thee - some of them are standing now and some mown down
  11,101,"We did not wrong them, but they wronged themselves. Their gods availed them naught, on which they called instead of God, when once the bidding of thy Lord had come; nor did they add save to their downfall"
  11,102,"Thus is thy Lord's overtaking when He overtakes the cities that have done wrong; verity, His overtaking is grievous, keen"
  11,103,"Verily, in that is a sign to him who fears the torment of the last day;- that is a day unto which men shall be gathered;- that is a witnessed day"
  11,104,"We will not delay it, save unto a numbered and appointed time"
  11,105,"The day when it shall come no soul shall speak save by His permission, and amongst them (shall be) the wretched and the glad"
  11,106,"And as for those who are wretched - why, in the Fire! there shall they groan and sob! to dwell therein for aye"
  11,107,"so long as the heavens and the earth endure; save what thy Lord will. Verily, thy Lord is one who works His will"
  11,108,"And as for those who are glad - why, in Paradise! to dwell therein for aye, so long as the heavens and the earth endure; save what thy Lord will,- a ceaseless boon"